{
  "texts": [
    "This novel application of LLM hallucination in cybersecurity represents a significant advancement, transforming a perceived limitation into a vital asset for strengthening digital security infrastructures.",
    "Just like in Alan Turing's \"Imitation Game\" where we have three characters an integrator and two individuals discussing a subject to identify who is a machine and who is a human.",
    "In our case we have predefined prompts acting as interrogators while two LLMs discussing the threat landscape for creating a cyber security scenario.",
    "We identified that our approach is suitable for generating new and unique cybersecurity exercise scenarios and can have other potential use cases.",
    "The structure of the remainder of this paper is organized as follows: Section (2) reviews the cyber security scenarios."
  ]
}